dbase_open opens a dBase database with the given access mode.
&note.open-basedir.func;

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    dbase 7.0.0

     The return value is now a resource instead of an
     int.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Opening a dBase database file


<?php

// open in read-only mode
$db = dbase_open('/tmp/test.dbf', 0);

if ($db) {
  // read some data ..

  dbase_close($db);
}

?>
